ArrayList: Resizable-array implementation of the List interface. Implements all optional list operations, and permits all elements, including null. Provides methods to manipulate the size of the array used internally to store the list. Runs various operations in constant or linear time.
Scanner: A simple text scanner which can parse primitive types and strings using regular expressions. Breaks input into tokens using a delimiter pattern, which by default matches whitespace. Can read text from any object implementing the Readable interface.
UUID: Represents an immutable universally unique identifier (UUID) with a 128-bit value. Describes the layout of a variant 2 (Leach-Salz) UUID and the different basic types of UUIDs.
Date: Represents a specific instant in time, with millisecond precision. Deprecated methods for interpreting dates as year, month, day, hour, minute, and second values. Reflects coordinated universal time (UTC) but may not do so exactly.
